Package com.android.interfaces

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Behaviour
    simple interface that has three abstract methods that any class that implements this interface have to override these methods
    Life
    This is Functional Interface, which means it has only ONE abstract method (it can have as many default or static methods as you like).
    Manners<T extends Animal,​V extends Life>
    T can be a Animal or one of the subclasses of Animal which are Elephant,Zebra,Cow.
    Move<T,​V>
    this interface has two generics T and V three classes implement the Move interface Robot implements and specifies the generic type to be used class Robot implements Move<Cow,Zebra> Vehicle implements and uses it's own generics to supply a type class Vehicle<U,X> implements Move<U,X> Car implments but does not specify any type class Car implements Move
